AWS Learning Through Documentation and Video Study


Introduction

This learning activity was performed to improve AWS cloud knowledge through documentation reading, video learning, AWS Console exploration, and concept revision. The session mainly focused on understanding AWS Lambda concepts and revising previously learned AWS services.

Objective

The objectives of this learning session were:

To continue AWS cloud learning.
To study AWS services using documentation and videos.
To understand AWS Lambda concepts.
To revise previously learned AWS services.
To improve understanding of AWS workflows and cloud architecture.
To maintain GitHub documentation for daily learning activities.
Learning Activities Performed
1. Studied AWS Documentation

Read AWS-related documentation to understand cloud services and workflows.

Topics explored:

AWS Lambda
IAM concepts
S3 permissions
SNS and SES workflows
CloudWatch monitoring

Purpose:

To understand AWS concepts using official documentation.
2. Watched AWS Learning Videos

Studied AWS concepts through learning videos.

Topics covered:

Serverless computing
Lambda triggers
Event-driven execution
AWS monitoring concepts

Purpose:

To improve practical understanding of AWS services and workflows.
3. Explored AWS Lambda Concepts

Learned about AWS Lambda service and serverless computing.

Topics learned:

Lambda functions
Triggers
Automatic scaling
Timeout concepts
Event-driven architecture

Purpose:

To understand how AWS runs code automatically without managing servers.
Lambda Workflow Studied

Trigger/Event → Lambda Function → Output

Examples of triggers explored:

S3 events
SNS notifications
API requests
CloudWatch events
Revision of Previously Learned AWS Services

Revised previously explored AWS services:

IAM
S3
IAM Policies
RDS
SNS
SES

Purpose:

To strengthen AWS cloud fundamentals.
AWS Console Exploration

Performed practical exploration inside AWS Console.

Activities included:

Exploring service dashboards
Viewing monitoring sections
Understanding AWS workflows visually

Purpose:

To improve practical AWS familiarity.
GitHub Documentation Work

Updated GitHub learning repository with:

AWS learning notes
Daily learning activities
AWS service documentation
Concept summaries

Purpose:

To maintain proper documentation and learning consistency.
Learnings
AWS documentation helps understand real cloud workflows and architecture.
Video learning improves practical understanding of AWS services.
AWS Lambda is a serverless compute service that runs code automatically based on triggers.
CloudWatch is used to monitor AWS services, logs, and execution metrics.
Continuous learning and documentation are important in DevOps and cloud environments.
Conclusion

This learning activity helped in improving AWS cloud understanding through documentation reading, video learning, AWS Console exploration, and concept revision. The session strengthened understanding of AWS Lambda, serverless computing, monitoring concepts, and AWS workflows while improving documentation practices for DevOps learning.

